Law: And let me thank you for not punishing my student, merely revoking her rights to study and having her leave the east.
Maeok: Please, don't thank me. I'm sorry I couldn't do more.
Maeok: The boat should be here soon. Are you going to the Kingdom of the Sun?
Law: Not just yet. I think I will travel with Yota, away from this depressing place, and take in some of the sights first.
Law: Yan-Bo will travel with us, too, before returning to his lake.
Yan-Bo: Pang, is there something you wished to discuss with me?
Pang: ...Well, it seems I cannot keep secrets from you, Master.
Yan-Bo: This note... it is from the tiger you once served, is it not?
Pang: It is, I recognized his handwriting right away. Whether he's alive or dead, this note could only mean...
Yan-Bo: Listen, Pang, we still have some time before the boat leaves. How about we spar?
Pang: But, Master, haven't you always said...
Yan-Bo: Before I would not instruct you, as my heart was tightly bound... but those knots have been untied. There are no restrictions anymore.
Pang: If that is the case, then... I await your instruction, Master!
Yan-Bo: Show me your moves!!
Yan-Bo: Pang, give it all you've got in the Martial Arts Tournament. Understand what it is that drives you.
Yan-Bo: And no matter the truth, whether Yao is alive or dead, do not let your demons control you any longer.
Law: Strange... have you seen my student, Yan-Bo? The boat is here, and yet she is not.
Yan-Bo: Is that so...
Miranda: Hey, lay off!
Panther Punk: You totally disgrace our talisman, then next minute you're running away!? We're not gonna let you get away that easy!
Vengeful Honey Badger: Yeah, and you messed up our boss big time!! Who says you can leave!?
Panther Punk: Eh... S-Spirit fog!?
Soohyeon: And spirit water, too~
Miranda: You guys... but how...
Toyokuni: If you want to thank us, then thank Juan-Yun. He knew someone'd end up giving you trouble, so he asked us to come help.
Miranda: But... why would you help me? We were never great friends...
Tindoiimu: ...I guess it's because we were part of the tournament together.
Soohyeon: Yeah, Tindoiimu's right.
Soohyeon: Even though we didn't spend much time together, contestants still look out for each other.
Panther Punk: Hmph!! Don't lump us in the same category as those slimy bugs and fur-less humans!
Vengeful Honey Badger: Come on, let's teach 'em a lesson! For the boss!!
Juan-Yun: Is Miranda okay?
Juan-Yun: I've been worried!
Toyokuni: ...Always the knight in shining armor.
Juan-Yun: Hey, it's what I do!
Juan-Yun: Anyway, Miranda's...?
Tindoiimu: She's fine. Let's get her on the boat.
Toyokuni: Yes, it should be about to leave.
Juan-Yun: Great~
Juan-Yun: If I were a bit faster I could have said goodbye.
Soohyeon: Oh yeah! I bet we could see her off from here...
Soohyeon: We can~! Quick, everyone get over here!
Soohyeon: There's the boat!
Soohyeon: ...She's gone.
Toyokuni: ...Yes.
Juan-Yun: ...It's a bit lonely, all of a sudden. Can you feel it too, Princess?
Tindoiimu: ...Why are you asking me?
Juan-Yun: Because Miranda's a human... her situation is similar to yours. I guess that's why you agreed to help her, right?
Tindoiimu: If we're done here, then I'll be going now.
Juan-Yun: These petals... they're from the Udumbara, aren't they?
Toyokuni: From here it doesn't look as if the Udumbara has flowered, though.
Juan-Yun: Maybe only these few flowers blossomed, and then the wind blew them over here?
Soohyeon: Maybe the Holy Dragon is praising us for a job well done~
Tindoiimu: ......
: If you spend time somewhere, and leave a piece of yourself there... that's home enough.

Tindoiimu: (And yet, how come I find this all so... strangely beautiful...)
